: Adding a “Wishlist” button to products.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Additional Features - Wishlist</title>
    <style>
        .product { margin: 20px; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid #ccc; width: 200px; }
        button { padding: 10px; background-color: #28a745; color: white; border: none; cursor: pointer; }
        button:hover { background-color: #218838; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Product with Wishlist Feature</h2>
    <div class="product">
        <h3>Smartphone</h3>
        <p>Price: $499</p>
        <button onclick="addToWishlist()">Add to Wishlist</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        function addToWishlist() {
            alert("Item added to wishlist!");
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>



: Hover effects and improved product card layout.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>UI/UX Improvements</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 50px; }
        .product-card {
            border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; width: 200px;
            transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
        }
        .product-card:hover { transform: scale(1.05); box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2); }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="product-card">
        <h3>Headphones</h3>
        <p>Price: $99</p>
        <p>High-quality sound with noise cancellation.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>



Fetch product data from a sample API (using fetch).
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>API Enhancements</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Products from API</h2>
    <ul id="product-list"></ul>

    <script>
        // Example API (dummy)
        const products = [
            {name: "Laptop", price: "$899"},
            {name: "Smartwatch", price: "$199"},
            {name: "Tablet", price: "$299"}
        ];

        const ul = document.getElementById("product-list");
        products.forEach(product => {
            const li = document.createElement("li");
            li.textContent = `${product.name} - ${product.price}`;
            ul.appendChild(li);
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>


: Lazy loading images for performance improvement.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Performance & Security</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Product Images (Lazy Load)</h2>
    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/200" loading="lazy" alt="Product 1">
    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/200" loading="lazy" alt="Product 2">
</body>
</html>



Simple input validation for product quantity.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Testing Enhancements</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Buy Product</h2>
    <label for="qty">Quantity:</label>
    <input type="number" id="qty" min="1" max="10">
    <button onclick="validateQty()">Add to Cart</button>

    <script>
        function validateQty() {
            const qty = document.getElementById("qty").value;
            if(qty < 1 || qty > 10) {
                alert("Quantity must be between 1 and 10");
            } else {
                alert("Added " + qty + " items to cart!");
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>



